3 Concepts
**********

A “priority cookie” is the bracketed text ‘[XY]’ that follows the ‘TODO’
keyword on an Org headline.

‘X’, the “group letter”
     A single uppercase letter from ‘A’ through ‘Z’.

‘Y’, the “rank”
     A non-negative integer.  Smaller means higher priority.  ‘Y’ may
     have one or more digits.  Sorting is numerical, so ‘C2’ outranks
     ‘C10’ which outranks ‘C100’.

Trailing asterisks
     Optional.  Zero or more ‘*’ characters that appear inside the
     brackets, immediately after the integer rank.  Asterisks mark extra
     urgency; see *note Urgency Asterisks::.


