7 The tasks.org File
********************

‘oltp-init-tasks-file’ writes a file with the structure:

     #+TITLE: Tasks
     #+STARTUP: showall
     #+LaTeX_HEADER: \usepackage[margin=0.5in]{geometry}

     * Do it today

     * Do it this week

     * Do it next week

     * Do it later this month

     * Do it next month

     * Do it in two months

     * Do it in three months

     * Do it in four months

     * Do it in five months

     * Do it in six months

     * Do it next year

Add ‘**’ subheadings under each section.  Once a section has its items
in declining priority order, select that region and run
‘oltp-prioritize-region’.  Blank lines start a new priority group inside
the region.

   To assign ‘SCHEDULED’ dates to every TODO in the file at once, run
‘oltp-schedule-tasks-file’.


