9 SQLite Project Database
*************************

The package prefers the built-in ‘sqlite’ library shipped with Emacs 29
or newer compiled with ‘--with-sqlite3’.  When the built-in library is
unavailable, the package falls back to the ‘sqlite3’ command-line shell.
Either backend is enough.

   The default expected schema looks like:

     CREATE TABLE projects (
         id               INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
         ProjectDirectory TEXT
     );

The table name is not significant when ‘oltp-db-table’ is ‘nil’; the
package detects whichever table contains the ‘ProjectDirectory’ column.
If you keep your projects in a different column, set ‘oltp-db-column’.
If multiple tables contain that column, set ‘oltp-db-table’ explicitly
to pin detection.

   Project names are de-duplicated and sorted before they are presented
to ‘completing-read’.


File: org-todo-letter-number-priorities.info,  Node: Tag Insertion,  Next: Keybindings,  Prev: SQLite Project Database,  Up: Top

10 Tag Insertion
****************

‘oltp-add-project-tag’ delegates to ‘org-set-tags’, so:

   • The new tag is added to the existing tag list rather than appended
     as a separate block.
   • Org's tag alignment column is respected.
   • The command is idempotent: re-running with the same project does
     not duplicate the tag.

   The project name returned by ‘oltp--read-project’ is sanitized into
an Org-compatible tag by replacing every character outside
‘[A-Za-z0-9_@%]’ with an underscore.


File: org-todo-letter-number-priorities.info,  Node: Keybindings,  Next: Testing,  Prev: Tag Insertion,  Up: Top

11 Keybindings
**************

The package does not bind any keys by default.  The following bindings
are a reasonable starting point.

     (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c j p") #'oltp-prioritize-region)
     (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c j s") #'oltp-strip-region)
     (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c j o") #'oltp-sort-region)
     (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c j t") #'oltp-add-project-tag)
     (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c j T") #'oltp-tag-region)
     (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c j i") #'oltp-init-tasks-file)
     (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c j d") #'oltp-schedule-tasks-file)


